  "title": "Amazon Q3 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-10-30T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q3",
  "location": "Seattle, WA",
  "url": "https://ir.aboutamazon.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "andy-jassy",
      "speaker_name": "Andy Jassy",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "AWS delivered another record quarter, growing 21% to $34.2 billion. We see AI workloads becoming a larger fraction of AWS revenue every quarter. Demand for inference compute is now exceeding training demand for the first time, which plays to our strength in Inferentia chips and our breadth of managed AI services. We expect AWS to finish 2025 with annual revenue well above our $120 billion target. Our logistics robotics network has now deployed over 1 million robots and is reducing fulfillment cost per unit by approximately 25%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "brian-olsavsky",
      "speaker_name": "Brian Olsavsky",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:20:00",
      "text": "Total net sales were $171.9 billion, up 11% year-over-year. AWS operating income was $13.6 billion, with a margin of 39.8%. North America segment operating income was $6.1 billion. For Q4, we are guiding net sales of $180–185 billion and operating income of $16–21 billion, which includes the typical seasonal step-up in fulfillment costs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Brian, AWS margin of 39.8% is impressive. Is this the new sustainable level, or do you expect capex to weigh on margins as infrastructure investments come online?"
    }
  ],
